Parabembras robinsoni is distinguished from its congeners in having usually 11 spines in the first dorsal fin (vs. 8-9 in P. curta and 9-10 in
P . multisquamata
), a distinct symphyseal knob in the lower jaw (vs. symphyseal knob absent in P. curta and P. multisquamata ), two preocular spines (vs. single in P. curta and P. multisquamata ), and single lachrymal spine (two in P. curta and P. multisquamata ).

Coloration. In fresh condition, head and body reddish orange, white ventrally; fins red, interradial membranes pale red; distal margins of dorsal and anal fins dark red; posterior half of caudal fin dark red [based on pl. E. Afr-97 of 
Ochiai (1976)
]. In preserved condition, head and body dark brown; fins pale gray; distal margin of second dorsal, anal and caudal fins dark brown.
